00:55:27,873 --> 00:55:32,273
手放せ 翼はついたから
Let go of it, for I have grown wings.

210
00:55:32,273 --> 00:55:38,373
さあ行こう 夜明けに舵を向けて
Now, let's go, steering the rudder towards the dawn.

211
00:56:17,773 --> 00:56:23,173
風に吹かれて 誰も気づかぬよう
Fanned by the wind, as if no one notices,

212
00:56:23,173 --> 00:56:29,073
区別がつかない モノクロの世界
a monochrome world that cannot be distinguished.

213
00:56:29,073 --> 00:56:35,073
色を足しても 何も見えなくて
Even if I add color, I cannot see anything,

214
00:56:35,073 --> 00:56:41,373
まるで私は 息を止めていた
as if I had stopped breathing.

215
00:56:46,173 --> 00:56:52,573
もういいよ 遠くても 叶えたい 私は
It's alright now, even if it's far, I want to make it come true...

216
00:56:52,573 --> 00:56:58,473
この世界 惑いも 抱きしめていたいのに
Even though I want to embrace the hesitations in this world,

217
00:56:58,473 --> 00:57:04,173
夢のキャンバスに 描き続ける意味は
the meaning of continuing to paint on the canvas of dreams...

218
00:57:04,173 --> 00:57:12,373
この胸に 輝いている ストーリー
is the story shining in this heart.

219
00:57:22,373 --> 00:57:30,373
溺れることに 意味などないけれど
There is no meaning in drowning, but...

220
00:57:30,373 --> 00:57:36,373
拾い集めた 欠片 失うの
will I lose the fragments I've gathered?

221
00:57:36,373 --> 00:57:44,373
そして夜は その冷たさを 溶かして手を伸ばした
And so, the night melted away that coldness and reached out its hand.

222
00:57:44,873 --> 00:57:50,873
もういいよ 遠くても 届けたい 私は
It's alright now, even if it's far, I want to reach you...

223
00:57:50,873 --> 00:57:56,573
抜け出す 涙も 抱きしめていたいのに
Even though I want to embrace the tears that escape...

224
00:57:56,573 --> 00:58:02,373
夢のキャンバスに 心込めるのは
putting my heart into the canvas of dreams...

225
00:58:02,373 --> 00:58:10,873
この空に 描き出していく ストーリー
is the story I will draw in this sky.

226
00:58:21,373 --> 00:58:31,373
そして夜は その冷たさを 溶かして手を伸ばして
And so, the night melted away that coldness, reaching out its hand...

227
00:58:31,373 --> 00:58:39,373
もういいの 遠くても 叶えたい 私の
It's enough now, even if it's far, I want to make it come true...

228
00:58:39,373 --> 00:58:44,373
この世界 言葉で包んだ
my world wrapped in words.

229
00:58:44,373 --> 00:58:49,373
夢のキャンバスに 色を足していく
Adding color to the canvas of dreams...

230
00:58:49,373 --> 00:58:55,373
この胸に 今輝いて
now shining in this heart.

231
00:58:55,373 --> 00:59:01,373
強くなくてもいい 壊れかけてもいい
It's fine if I'm not strong, it's fine if I'm breaking,

232
00:59:01,373 --> 00:59:07,373
この心は 永久に羽ばたいて
this heart will flap its wings for eternity.

233
00:59:07,373 --> 00:59:15,873
響くように 塗り替えていく 私色
I'll repaint it in my own colors so it resonates.

234
00:59:43,373 --> 00:59:49,173
Hello, everyone!

235
00:59:49,373 --> 00:59:54,873
It is Day 2 of Drawn to Dawn!

236
00:59:58,373 --> 01:00:06,373
Yes, yes. Welcome to Day 2 of Takanashi Kiara and Ninomae Ina'nis' first concert, Drawn to Dawn!

237
01:00:04,896 --> 01:00:07,196
Are you guys enjoying the show so far?

238
01:00:07,196 --> 01:00:10,996
Yay!

239
01:00:10,996 --> 01:00:13,396
Ah, you know, I was really...

240
01:00:13,396 --> 01:00:18,396
I want to talk about Tako Tako first because...

241
01:00:18,396 --> 01:00:24,296
...yesterday, I heard you guys sing along to the instrumental...

242
01:00:24,296 --> 01:00:28,596
...and I was like, "Ah, I feel bad for not singing on Day 1."

243
01:00:28,596 --> 01:00:32,396
But you know, I knew I was opening for, you know, Day 2...

244
01:00:32,396 --> 01:00:36,396
...so I kind of thought of a better song to open than Tako Tako.

245
01:00:36,396 --> 01:00:41,396
So, hope you guys had fun singing it! Thank you again!

246
01:00:43,896 --> 01:00:47,396
And of course, I sang two of my senpais' songs...

247
01:00:47,396 --> 01:00:53,396
...Senchou's Dead Man's Chest and Towa-senpai's Palette.

248
01:00:53,396 --> 01:00:58,896
Oh, I specifically... I specifically wanted to...

249
01:00:58,896 --> 01:01:01,396
...choose their songs...

250
01:01:01,396 --> 01:01:06,896
...because they are, you know, senpais that I really look up to.

251
01:01:06,896 --> 01:01:09,896
And I always feel like...

252
01:01:09,896 --> 01:01:16,696
...my journey here wouldn't have been possible if I didn't discover my senpais many, many years ago.

253
01:01:16,696 --> 01:01:20,396
And I always, you know, wanted to pay respect to...

254
01:01:20,396 --> 01:01:22,896
...the path they paved for us.

255
01:01:22,896 --> 01:01:25,896
So, yeah, I hope you guys enjoyed it!

256
01:01:25,896 --> 01:01:29,896
I'm so nervous again!

257
01:01:29,896 --> 01:01:32,396
Yeah.

258
01:01:32,396 --> 01:01:35,896
And, um, you know, I...

259
01:01:35,896 --> 01:01:39,396
...of course, didn't really tell you guys specifically what penlight colors to use...

260
01:01:39,396 --> 01:01:43,896
...but I knew you guys would get my message because we share a brain cell, right? Right?

261
01:01:47,896 --> 01:01:49,896
Yeah! So, well...

262
01:01:49,896 --> 01:01:56,396
...now going by the different setlist, because we, you know, have different setlist for Day 1 and Day 2...

263
01:01:56,396 --> 01:02:01,896
...so, you know, going by the process of elimination...

264
01:02:01,896 --> 01:02:04,896
...we have a couple of songs from my new EP left. Actually, who...

265
01:02:04,896 --> 01:02:08,396
...bought my EP?!

266
01:02:08,396 --> 01:02:12,396
Yay! Thank you so much!

267
01:02:12,396 --> 01:02:16,396
I hope you were lucky to get an autograph. I tried to sign as much as possible, but...

268
01:02:16,396 --> 01:02:21,396
...I knew, you know, sometimes you can't be lucky.

269
01:02:21,396 --> 01:02:25,896
Thank you, thank you! But yeah, I want you guys to have even more fun than before today.

270
01:02:25,896 --> 01:02:30,396
I mean, you always have fun, so that's good, but, yeah!

271
01:02:30,396 --> 01:02:33,896
And, you know, sing along, have fun, and...

272
01:02:33,896 --> 01:02:39,896
...I always think that a live stage is where not only me performing is creating...

273
01:02:39,896 --> 01:02:43,896
...the performance, but you guys as well. You really help...

274
01:02:44,396 --> 01:02:47,896
...you know, help everyone with that special experience.

275
01:02:47,896 --> 01:02:52,896
So let's create an unforgettable memory together today, okay?!

276
01:02:52,896 --> 01:02:57,896
Yay!

277
01:02:57,896 --> 01:03:00,396
Anyways, um...

278
01:03:00,396 --> 01:03:07,396
...I would also like to shout out to those watching at home and at the live viewings in the cinema. Hello! Hello to you again!

279
01:03:07,396 --> 01:03:10,896
And also...

280
01:03:10,896 --> 01:03:18,396
...the lovely, lovely girls doing a watch-along right now. Hi, guys! Thank you! Bae, IRyS, and everyone else...

281
01:03:18,396 --> 01:03:21,896
...doing the watch-along, thank you, thank you!

282
01:03:21,896 --> 01:03:27,396
Um, you know, I'm always amazed by everyone's support...

283
01:03:27,396 --> 01:03:34,396
...and really, without the support of HoloEN members as well, like, I wouldn't have had...

284
01:03:34,396 --> 01:03:39,396
...the confidence to stand here today. Thank you, I love you!

285
01:03:43,896 --> 01:03:49,896
And of course, I would like to remind you guys about the hashtag for today's concert as well: #TakoToriFirstConcert, as usual.

286
01:03:49,896 --> 01:03:53,896
Post your thoughts about it, post the screenshots, no videos! No videos!

287
01:03:58,896 --> 01:04:04,896
Post the screenshots, and, you know, whenever we have time, we've been checking the hashtag, and of course, after...

288
01:04:04,896 --> 01:04:10,396
...as well. I want to hear what you guys thought about the live, so, yeah!

289
01:04:10,396 --> 01:04:13,896
Thank you, thank you!

290
01:04:13,896 --> 01:04:17,396
And, unlike yesterday...

291
01:04:17,396 --> 01:04:23,896
...first MC means I, unfortunately, have to...

292
01:04:23,896 --> 01:04:28,896
...bid farewell to those watching the sneak peek on YouTube. I'm sorry.

293
01:04:28,896 --> 01:04:32,896
But, if you want to keep the party going...

294
01:04:33,396 --> 01:04:39,896
...head to the streaming site via the description, the comment... I don't know where the comment is.

295
01:04:42,896 --> 01:04:47,896
But I know that some of you guys won't get a chance to see my new outfit that I revealed yesterday, so...

296
01:04:47,896 --> 01:04:52,896
...I thought, maybe, I'll do something... um, maybe you guys can help me...

297
01:04:52,896 --> 01:04:58,896
...transition into the new costume here...

298
01:04:58,896 --> 01:05:03,396
...so that even those of you...

299
01:05:02,776 --> 01:05:05,076
...and on YouTube, teammates can see.

300
01:05:05,076 --> 01:05:08,776
All right, so I'm gonna count down from three. Countdown with me, okay?

301
01:05:08,776 --> 01:05:12,276
And then we'll switch into the new outfit for you guys to see.

302
01:05:12,276 --> 01:05:13,776
Ready?

303
01:05:13,776 --> 01:05:17,376
Ready? Give me a "one" if you're ready!

304
01:05:17,376 --> 01:05:19,776
All right, all right, all right.

305
01:05:19,776 --> 01:05:22,076
All right, here we go!

306
01:05:22,076 --> 01:05:25,776
Three, two, one, ha!

307
01:05:28,276 --> 01:05:30,276
Ta-da!

308
01:05:30,776 --> 01:05:32,776
Thank you, thank you, thank you!

309
01:05:36,276 --> 01:05:39,276
All right, it's time to move on to the next song.

310
01:05:39,276 --> 01:05:44,276
And I think this song also fits the starry stage perfectly.

311
01:05:44,276 --> 01:05:46,976
No, not that one yet, but...

312
01:05:46,976 --> 01:05:50,576
...this one is from one of my favorite franchises.

313
01:05:50,576 --> 01:05:52,576
So I hope you guys listen.

314
01:05:52,576 --> 01:05:55,776
Anyways, the song will fit the starry stage perfectly.

315
01:05:55,776 --> 01:05:57,776
Please give it a listen.

316
01:06:03,776 --> 01:06:17,776
無料パートは終了いたしました。ご視聴ありがとうございました！
The sneak peek part of the show has ended. Thank you for watching.

317
01:10:01,452 --> 01:12:55,452
無料パートは終了いたしました。ご視聴ありがとうございました！
The free portion of the show has ended. Thank you for watching!

